/Users/anthony/Programming/Deniable/sdp/prd-snapshot.md:549:### Why .vox format for assets + custom binary for chunk diffs?
/Users/anthony/Programming/Deniable/sdp/prd-snapshot.md:551:`.vox` is the right format for *assets* (compact, palette-aware, wide tooling). But chunk diffs over WebSocket need a different shape — they reference world coordinates not asset-local ones, encode incremental destruction events, and need to be tiny (10-50KB per significant event). The custom format question is DN-042 (an ADR).
/Users/anthony/Programming/Deniable/sdp/prd-snapshot.md:567:Phase 1's MVP is "developer plays it on their Mac." E2E framework setup (Playwright + harness) is a significant lift that delivers little vs. the developer playtesting directly. Add Phase 3+ if a build pipeline justifies it.
