ification report.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: [Issue — severity: blocking/minor] (seen 3x).\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: `~/Programming/VoxelPlayground/` — asset-pipeline spike whose recommendation feeds Deniable's `assets/pipeline/` module (seen 3x).\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: **Phase 1 — First Playable.** Voxel-aware end-to-end raid loop: 3 archetypes (Assaulter / Marksman / Drone Operator), 4 weapons, 2 drones (Spotter / Strike), 1 voxel courtyard map, rule-based AI, minimal hideout (Stash + Roster + 1 trader), open-ended clock only, no narrative integration. The developer can play a Deniable raid on their Mac. (seen 3x).\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: **Phase 2 — Engine Completion.** All 9 archetypes, all 6 drone classes, full weapon/equipment/sensor/EW catalog, 5 clock types, LLM tactical AI (Anthropic Haiku 4.5 / Sonnet 4.6 / Opus 4.7 tiered), all 6 factions, Recovery roll system, 2-3 maps. (seen 3x).\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: **Phase 3 — Hideout & Campaign Layer.** Full hideout UI (all 9 screens), hideout tier progression, faction reputation, traders with rotating inventory, crafting, narrative engine integration via DeniableTranslator + `deniable_event_cycle.py`, Three-Act scaffolding, Free Raids vs Story Raids framework, full campaign save/load. (seen 3x).\n"}
