/Users/anthony/Programming/Deniable/sdp/verification/t-006@20260502t001433za-verify.md:81:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:43:18.804Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777686198804_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-006 @sdp/verification/t-006 @20260502t001433za-verify.md\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-05-01\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** `src/deniable/narrative/world_bridge.py`, `tests/test_world_bridge.py`, `src/deniable/settings.py`, `pyproject.toml`, `sdp/implementation-plan.md`, `deniable_narrative_integration_v1.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of `WorldBridge` correctly exposes the required methods: `health()`, `get_world_entities(domain=...)`, and `next_beat(...)`. The method signatures match the requirements, and the use of `httpx.Client` correctly implements the requested HTTP client functionality. Dataclasses (`HealthStatus`, `WorldEntity`, `StoryBeat`) correctly model the cypherclaw narrative service schema as described in the integration documents.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task is mostly complete. The bridge handles base URL, timeout, and authentication headers correctly via the application settings. However, the specification file `specs/t-006 @20260502t001433za-spec.md` cited in the task instructions is missing from the repository. While the requirements were reconstructible from the PRD and implementation plan, the absence of the spec file is a gap in the Tier 2 documentation requirements.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows the established project structure and naming conventions. The use of `DomainFilter` type hints ensures consistency with the domain tagging rules defined in `deniable_narrative_integration_v1.md`.\n\n## Security\nThe bridge correctly handles sensitive information by using `DENIABLE_NARRATIVE_AUTH_TOKEN` from environment-based settings and passing it via the `X-Narrative-Auth` header. No secrets are hardcoded in the source or tests.\n\n## Quality\nThe code quality is high, with clear docstrings referencing the narrative API PRD (CN-003, CN-005, CN-006). The tests are comprehensive, covering happy paths, error handling, and context manager behavior. Coverage for `world_bridge.py` is at 90%.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: minor] Missing specification file `specs/t-006 @20260502t001433za-spec.md`.\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: minor] `WorldBridge` does not implement structured logging. Task T-001 requires all backend modules to emit structured JSON logs using `structlog`, which is especially relevant for outbound HTTP calls in a service bridge.\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: minor] `WorldBridge` is implemented as a synchronous client. While not explicitly forbidden by the task, FastAPI endpoints are typically asynchronous, and using a synchronous client may lead to event loop blocking in future integration.\n\n## Verdict: PASS WITH NOTES\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n- Please commit the missing spec file `specs/t-006 @20260502t001433za-spec.md`.\n- Consider adding `structlog` calls to `WorldBridge` for better observability of narrative service interactions.\n- Consider providing an asynchronous version of the bridge if it is intended to be called from the main FastAPI request path.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-006 @20260502t001433za-verify.md"}}
